    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The executive committee of the\nirrigation congress in its report\nmade to the session at noon today\npaid high compliment to the man\nner in which Spokane and the board\nof control Of the seventeenth con-\ngress have managed all prepare.\ntions for the gathering.\n\n\nThe committee says the Spokane\ngentlemen have set a high standard\nfor all cities that may hereafter get\nthe convention, to follow. The com\nmittee expressed its sincere thanks\nto the board of control and ratified\nall Of its actions.\n\n\nOn motion of Governor Gooding\nof Idaho. seconded by Governor\nHay of Washington, the report of\nthe executive committee. which also\nlays down the rules of procedure\nfor the congress, was adopted."
    }
